# image-processing / sharp

`sharp` is the fastest Node.js image-processing module — a libvips binding that reads JPEG/PNG/WebP/AVIF/GIF/TIFF/SVG and writes raster image files. In OOTA it authors a raster **image** deliverable deterministically and headlessly: build a pixel buffer (or load an input), resize/recolor/composite/format-convert, and write it via `.toFile()`. Prebuilt binaries ship for macOS arm64+x64, so no system libvips is needed.

