## Required reading

- sharp official docs (pixelplumbing, Apache-2.0, Lovell Fuller & contributors): https://sharp.pixelplumbing.com/
- anthropics/skills (official Agent Skills repo, Anthropic — no dedicated sharp skill): https://github.com/anthropics/skills
- travisvn/awesome-claude-skills (community list): https://github.com/travisvn/awesome-claude-skills

## Render

```bash
# install (local — never via global NODE_PATH)
mkdir -p out && npm init -y >/dev/null 2>&1 && npm install sharp

# generate the image
node gen.mjs   # calls sharp(...).<format>().toFile('out/image.<ext>')
```

## Failure modes

- ESM `ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND`: install sharp locally in the project; do not resolve a global install via `NODE_PATH`.
- `./package.json` export is blocked — read the version another way, not via `require('sharp/package.json')`.
- Operations are async (Promise-based) — `await .toFile()` before reading metadata.
- Codec defaults shift across libvips versions — pin compression effort/quality explicitly for reproducible builds.
- Requires Node `^18.17.0` or `>=20.3.0` (Node-API v9).
